# Supabase Configuration
# Get these values from your Supabase project dashboard: https://app.supabase.com/project/_/settings/api

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anonymous-public-key-here

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Copy this file to .env in the same directory
# 2. Replace the placeholder values with your actual Supabase credentials
# 3. Never commit the .env file to version control (already in .gitignore)
# 4. The anon key is safe to expose in client-side code (it's public)
# 5. DO NOT put your service_role key here - it should never be in client code

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SECURITY NOTES
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# • VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY is the public/anonymous key (safe for frontend)
# • Row Level Security (RLS) policies protect your data, not key secrecy
# • Service role key should ONLY be used in backend/server environments
# • Rotate keys regularly via Supabase dashboard → Settings → API
